<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Samuel 8:1-18</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="24">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="18">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about afterward that David proceeded to strike the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines down and subdue them, and David got to take Meth&acute;eg-am&acute;mah out of the hand of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And he went on to strike down the Mo&acute;ab&middot;ites and measure them with a line, making them lie down on the earth, that he might measure two lines to put them to death, and a full line to preserve them alive; and the Mo&acute;ab&middot;ites came to be David’s servants to carry tribute.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And David went on to strike down Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer the son of Re&acute;hob the king of Zo&acute;bah as he was going his way to put his control back again at the river Eu&middot;phra&acute;tes.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And David got to capture from him one thousand seven hundred horsemen and twenty thousand men on foot; and David proceeded to hamstring all the chariot horses, but he let a hundred chariot horses of them remain.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">When Syria of Damascus came to help Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer the king of Zo&acute;bah, David then struck down among the Syrians twenty-two thousand men.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Further, David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus; and the Syrians came to be David’s servants to carry tribute. And Jehovah continued to save David wherever he went.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Moreover, David took the circular shields of gold that happened to be on the servants of Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer and brought them to Jerusalem.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And from Be&acute;tah and Be&middot;ro&acute;thai, cities of Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer, King David took copper in very great quantity.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Now To&acute;i the king of Ha&acute;math got to hear that David had struck down all the military force of Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">So To&acute;i sent Jo&acute;ram his son to King David to ask him about his welfare and congratulate him over the fact that he had fought against Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer so that he struck him down (for Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer had become trained in warfare against To&acute;i); and in his hand there proved to be articles of silver and articles of gold and articles of copper.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">These also King David sanctified to Jehovah, together with the silver and the gold that he had sanctified from all the nations that he had subdued,</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">from Syria and from Mo&acute;ab and from the sons of Am&acute;mon and from the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and from Am&acute;a&middot;lek and from the spoil of Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer the son of Re&acute;hob the king of Zo&acute;bah.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And David proceeded to make a name when he came back from striking down the E&acute;dom&middot;ites in the Valley of Salt—eighteen thousand.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And he kept garrisons placed in E&acute;dom. In all E&acute;dom he placed garrisons, and all the E&acute;dom&middot;ites came to be servants of David; and Jehovah kept saving David wherever he went.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And David kept reigning over all Israel; and David was continually rendering judicial decision and righteousness for all his people.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And Jo&acute;ab the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah was over the army; and Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat the son of A&middot;hi&acute;lud was recorder.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And Za&acute;dok the son of A&middot;hi&acute;tub and A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech the son of A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar were priests, and Se&middot;rai&acute;ah was secretary.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da [was over] the Cher&acute;e&middot;thites and the Pel&acute;e&middot;thites. As for the sons of David, they became priests.</span>
</p>
</form>

