<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Samuel 23:1-39</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="24">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="39">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And these are the last words of David:<br><span class="p">“The utterance of David the son of Jes&acute;se,</span><br><span class="z">And the utterance of the able-bodied man that was raised up on high,</span><br><span class="p">The anointed of the God of Jacob,</span><br><span class="z">And the pleasant one of the melodies of Israel.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">The spirit of Jehovah it was that spoke by me,<br><span class="z">And his word was upon my tongue.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">The God of Israel said,<br><span class="z">To me the Rock of Israel spoke,</span><br><span class="p">‘When one ruling over mankind is righteous,</span><br><span class="z">Ruling in the fear of God,</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Then it is as the light of morning, when the sun shines forth,<br><span class="z">A morning without clouds.</span><br><span class="z">From brightness, from rain, there is grass out of the earth.’</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">For is not my household like that with God?<br><span class="z">Because it is an indefinitely lasting covenant that he has assigned to me,</span><br><span class="z">Nicely put in order in everything and secured.</span><br><span class="p">Because it is all my salvation and all my delight,</span><br><span class="z">Is that not why he will make it grow?</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">But good-for-nothing persons are chased away, like thornbushes, all of them;<br><span class="z">For it is not by the hand that they should be taken.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">When a man touches them<br><span class="z">He should be fully armed with iron and the shaft of a spear,</span><br><span class="z">And with fire they will thoroughly be burned up.”</span></span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">These are the names of the mighty men that belonged to David: Jo&acute;sheb-bas&middot;she&acute;beth a Tah&middot;che&acute;mo&middot;nite, the head of the three. He was brandishing his spear over eight hundred slain at one time.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Next to him El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar the son of Do&acute;do the son of A&middot;ho&acute;hi was among the three mighty men with David when they taunted the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines. They had gathered themselves there for the battle, and so the men of Israel retreated.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">He it was that rose up and kept striking down the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines until his hand wearied and his hand kept cleaving to the sword, so that Jehovah performed a great salvation on that day; and as for the people, they returned behind him only to strip [those struck down].</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And next to him was Sham&acute;mah the son of A&acute;gee the Har&acute;a&middot;rite. And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines proceeded to gather themselves to Le&acute;hi, where there then happened to be a tract of the field full of lentils; and the people themselves fled because of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">But he took his stand in the middle of the tract and delivered it and kept striking down the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, so that Jehovah performed a great salvation.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And three of the thirty head ones proceeded to go down and come at [the] harvest, to David at the cave of A&middot;dul&acute;lam; and a tent village of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines was encamped in the low plain of the Reph&acute;a&middot;im.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And David was then in the place hard to approach; and an outpost of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines was then in Beth&acute;le&middot;hem.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">After a while David expressed his craving and said: “O that I might have a drink of the water from the cistern of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem that is at the gate!”</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">At that the three mighty men forced their way into the camp of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and drew water from the cistern of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem that is at the gate and came carrying and bringing it to David; and he did not consent to drink it, but poured it out to Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And he went on to say: “It is unthinkable on my part, O Jehovah, that I should do this! [Shall I drink] the blood of the men going at the risk of their souls?” And he did not consent to drink it.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs17-2">These are the things the three mighty men did.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">As for A&middot;bish&acute;ai the brother of Jo&acute;ab the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah, he was the head of the thirty, and he was brandishing his spear over three hundred slain ones, and he had a reputation like the three.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">Although he was distinguished even more than the rest of the thirty, and he came to be their chief, to the rank of the [first] three he did not come.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">As for Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da the son of a valiant man, who did many deeds in Kab&acute;ze&middot;el, he himself struck down the two sons of Ar&acute;i&middot;el of Mo&acute;ab; and he himself descended and struck down a lion inside a waterpit on a day of snowfall.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And he it was that struck down the Egyptian man that was of extraordinary size. Though there was a spear in the hand of the Egyptian, yet he went on down to him with a rod and snatched the spear away from the Egyptian’s hand and killed him with his own spear.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">These things Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da did; and he had a reputation like the three mighty men.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Although he was distinguished even more than the thirty, to the rank of the three he did not come; but David appointed him to his own bodyguard.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">As&acute;a&middot;hel the brother of Jo&acute;ab was among the thirty; El&middot;ha&acute;nan the son of Do&acute;do of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem,</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">Sham&acute;mah the Ha&acute;rod&middot;ite, E&middot;li&acute;ka the Ha&acute;rod&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">He&acute;lez the Pal&acute;tite, I&acute;ra the son of Ik&acute;kesh the Te&middot;ko&acute;ite,</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">Abi-e&acute;zer the An&acute;a&middot;thoth&middot;ite, Me&middot;bun&acute;nai the Hu&acute;shath&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">Zal&acute;mon the A&middot;ho&acute;hite, Ma&acute;ha&middot;rai the Ne&middot;toph&acute;a&middot;thite,</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">He&acute;leb the son of Ba&acute;a&middot;nah the Ne&middot;toph&acute;a&middot;thite, It&acute;tai the son of Ri&acute;bai of Gib&acute;e&middot;ah of the sons of Benjamin,</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Be&middot;nai&acute;ah a Pir&acute;a&middot;thon&middot;ite, Hid&acute;dai of the torrent valleys of Ga&acute;ash,</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">A&acute;bi-al&acute;bon the Ar&acute;bath&middot;ite, Az&acute;ma&middot;veth the Bar-hu&acute;mite,</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">E&middot;li&acute;ah&middot;ba the Sha&middot;al&acute;bo&middot;nite, the sons of Ja&acute;shen, Jon&acute;a&middot;than,</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">Sham&acute;mah the Har&acute;a&middot;rite, A&middot;hi&acute;am the son of Sha&acute;rar the Har&acute;a&middot;rite,</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">E&middot;liph&acute;e&middot;let the son of A&middot;has&acute;bai the son of the Ma&middot;ac&acute;a&middot;thite, E&middot;li&acute;am the son of A&middot;hith&acute;o&middot;phel the Gi&acute;lon&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">Hez&acute;ro the Car&acute;mel&middot;ite, Pa&acute;a&middot;rai the Ar&acute;bite,</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">I&acute;gal the son of Nathan of Zo&acute;bah, Ba&acute;ni the Gad&acute;ite,</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Ze&acute;lek the Am&acute;mon&middot;ite, Na&acute;ha&middot;rai the Be&middot;er&acute;oth&middot;ite, armor-bearers of Jo&acute;ab the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah,</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">I&acute;ra the Ith&acute;rite, Ga&acute;reb the Ith&acute;rite,</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">U&middot;ri&acute;ah the Hit&acute;tite—thirty-seven in all.</span>
</p>
</form>

